# MDX Template Guide

> Authoring conventions for Allegion Developer Portal documentation using Astro + MDX.

This guide defines the MDX syntax conventions that produce HTML output matching the Allegion Developer Portal styling (Bootstrap + custom CSS).

---

## Front Matter

Every MDX file begins with YAML front matter:

```yaml
---
layout: ../layouts/DocLayout.astro
title: "Page Title"
subtitle: "Optional subtitle"
lastModified: "MM.DD.YYYY"
---
```

After the front matter, import the components you need:

```mdx
---
layout: ../layouts/DocLayout.astro
title: "Page Title"
---

import Panel from "../components/Panel.astro";
import Badge from "../components/Badge.astro";
import Steps from "../components/Steps.astro";
import Image from "../components/Image.astro";
import ImageGrid from "../components/ImageGrid.astro";
import Accordion from "../components/Accordion.astro";
import Mermaid from "../components/Mermaid.astro";
```

---

## Headings

Standard Markdown headings. For anchor links, use explicit HTML IDs:

```mdx
## Overview

<h3 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h3>
```

The explicit `id` attribute ensures anchor links like `#getting-started` work correctly.

