## Process Flow Diagrams (Mermaid)

Use the `<Mermaid>` component for flowcharts:

```mdx
<Mermaid chart={`
flowchart LR
    A[Start] --> B[Step 1]
    B --> C[Step 2]
    C --> D[Step 3]
    D --> E[Complete]

    style A fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
    style B fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
    style C fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
    style D fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
    style E fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
`} />
```

### Mermaid Node Types

| Syntax      | Shape        | Example              |
| ----------- | ------------ | -------------------- |
| `[text]`    | Rectangle    | `A[Process Step]`    |
| `((text))`  | Circle       | `A((Start))`         |
| `{text}`    | Diamond      | `A{Decision?}`       |
| `([text])`  | Stadium      | `A([Database])`      |

### Clickable Nodes

```mdx
<Mermaid chart={`
flowchart LR
    A[Documentation] --> B[Support Portal]

    click A href "/docs" "View Docs"
    click B href "https://support.example.com" "Get Help" _blank

    style A fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
    style B fill:#CD6620,stroke:#CD6620,color:#fff
`} />
```

### Mermaid Notes

- Use `fill:#CD6620` for Allegion orange brand color
- Use `color:#fff` for white text on colored backgrounds
- Add `_blank` to open links in new tabs
- Diagrams render with rounded corners automatically

