## Complete Example

```mdx
---
layout: ../layouts/DocLayout.astro
title: "API Integration Guide"
subtitle: "Getting started with the Allegion API"
lastModified: "02.26.2026"
---

import Panel from "../components/Panel.astro";
import Badge from "../components/Badge.astro";
import Steps from "../components/Steps.astro";
import Accordion from "../components/Accordion.astro";

# API Integration Guide

### Getting started with the Allegion API

*Last modified: 02.26.2026*

This guide covers the basics of integrating with the Allegion API.

<Panel type="info" title="Prerequisites">
You'll need a developer account and API key to follow this guide.
</Panel>

## Overview

<h3 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h3>

Follow these steps to make your first API call:

<Steps>
  <li><strong>Register</strong> - Create a developer account.</li>
  <li><strong>Get Credentials</strong> - Generate an API key.</li>
  <li><strong>Test</strong> - Make your first request.</li>
</Steps>

<Panel type="success" title="Ready to Go">
Once you have your API key, you can start making requests immediately.
</Panel>

## FAQ

<Accordion id="faq1" title="Where do I find my API key?">
Navigate to Settings > API Keys in the developer portal.
</Accordion>
```

